Message on screenL `M. Fil Imon` inhibit. We checked: parameter 213 - Mag. I monitor was 0A, Mag V monitor was 13V. This could potentialy be caused by a broken filament. We measeure the filament resistance including the cabling (resistance) with a multimeter from the PSU. We measured 77 ohm. This seemed a lot. A direct measurement without the cable gave a value of 7 ohm. This made us suspicies to the cabling/connector. When inspecting the connectors the blue connector going to the gun/magnetron filament filter unit. Was burned. problem started 20240506 7:30 and was resolved at 20240507 13:00
